Usage: add_line_end_track [-help] [-eol_width <float>] -layer <string>
                          -offset <float> [-track_distance <float>]
                          [-track_pitch <float>] [-except_eol_spacing <float> [-within <float>]]

-help                           # Prints out the command usage
-eol_width <float>              # eol width (float, optional)
-except_eol_spacing <float>     # spacing of the eol edge and a neighbor wire
                                # to exempt the rule (float, optional)
-layer <string>                 # layer the track to be created on
                                # (string, required)
-offset <float>                 # offset to core boundary (float, required)
-track_distance <float>         # distance between two sets of track
                                # (float, optional)
-track_pitch <float>            # track pitch (float, optional)
-within <float>                 # extension in orthogonal direction to find a
                                # neighbor wire (float, optional)